<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-755-675  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 755 675.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Banking  July 1989 v6 n7 p34(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Are bankers putting automated telemarketing on hold? (includesrelated article on Pittsburgh National Bank's automated outboundtelemarketing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Helm, Sylvia.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Automated telemarketing in the banking industry has yet to becomewidely used despite success stories.andP;  Industry insiders cite aprejudice against telemarketing in general.andP;  Automatic inboundtelemarketing can provide customer access to bank data bases usingpersonal identification codes; automatic number identification,which identifies incoming callers and accesses customer accountinformation in 1/50th of a second; and automatic calldistribution.andP;  Automatic outbound telemarketing provides outboundcall management, automated dialing and a call distribution systemthat only passes on live calls to the operators.andP;  On-screenscripts for cross-selling and order taking are also available, asis the ability to automatically segment or target the customerdata base.andP;  Several brief case studies of successfulimplementations are presented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelemarketingAutomationBankingAutomatic AnsweringAutomatic Call DistributorsAutomatic DialingMarketing Strategy.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>